Overview

This Rmd documents the code used and generates visualizations for the microbiome network in the manuscript Network-based differences in the vaginal and bladder microbial communities between women with and without urgency urinary incontinence by Nardos et al.

Define functions

#' Get named edge list
#'
#' The tidygraph interface will conveniently link the nodes and edge information
#' together. However, extracting both together in an edge list is not straight
#' forward. This function extracts this edge list to explore further.
#'
#' @param tg tidygraph-class object
#'
#' @return data.frame
#' @export
#'
#' @examples
#' named_edges <- get_edge_list(tg)
get_edge_list <- function(tg) {
  tg_nodes <-
    tg %>%
    activate(nodes) %>%
    data.frame() %>%
    rownames_to_column("rowid") %>%
    mutate(rowid = as.integer(rowid))
  tg_edges <-
    tg %>%
    activate(edges) %>%
    data.frame()

  named_edge_list <-
    tg_edges %>%
    # Rename from nodes
    left_join(tg_nodes, by = c("from" = "rowid")) %>%
    select(to, from, weight, pval,
           Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus, sequence) %>%
    rename_with(function(x) { paste0("from_", x) }, -to) %>%

    # Rename to nodes
    left_join(tg_nodes, by = c("to" = "rowid")) %>%
    select(to, starts_with("from_"),
           Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus, sequence) %>%
    rename_with(function(x) { paste0("to_", x) },
                -starts_with("from")) %>%

    # Clean up
    rename(weight = from_weight, pval = from_pval)

  named_edge_list
}

By community and size

gg_ur_community_size <- 
  (layout_ur_uui %>%
   ggraph() +
   geom_edge_link(alpha = 0.35) +
   geom_node_point(aes(colour = c_infomap, size = c_n_btwnn),
                   # size = 6,
                   show.legend = FALSE) +
   theme_graph() +
   ggtitle("UUI cases") +
   scale_size_continuous(range = c(3, 8)) +
   scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Set1")) +
  
  (layout_ur_ctrl %>%
     ggraph() +
     geom_edge_link(alpha = 0.35) +
     geom_node_point(aes(colour = c_infomap, size = c_n_btwnn),
                     # size = 6,
                     show.legend = FALSE) +
     theme_graph() +
     ggtitle("Controls") +
     scale_size_continuous(range = c(3, 8)) +
     scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Set2"))
plot(gg_ur_community_size)
